import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['speed'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['speed'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    heatmap = sns.heatmap(data.pivot_table(values='speed', index='latitude', columns='longitude'), cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt=".2f", cbar_kws={'label': 'Wind Speed'})
    heatmap.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    heatmap.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    heatmap.set_title('What is the distribution of wind speed by latitude and longitude?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="dirCat", y="speed", data=data, ci=None, color="b")
    plt.title("What is the average wind speed by wind direction category?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Wind Direction Category")
    plt.ylabel("Average Wind Speed")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
